# Azure DevOps Repository

This repository is hosted on **Azure DevOps**, not GitHub.

## Pull Requests

- NEVER use `gh` (GitHub CLI) for PRs, issues, or any repo operations — it will fail
- Use the **Azure DevOps MCP** (`user-Azure DevOps`) for all PR operations:
  - `repo_create_pull_request` — create PRs
  - `repo_get_pull_request_by_id` — read PR details
  - `repo_list_pull_request_threads` — read PR comments
  - `repo_create_pull_request_thread` — add PR comments
  - `repo_vote_pull_request` — approve / request changes
  - `repo_update_pull_request` — update PR settings (auto-complete, etc.)
  - `repo_update_pull_request_reviewers` — add/remove reviewers
  - `repo_get_pull_request_changes` — view PR diff

## Project Defaults

Read `.meitheal.config.json` for `organization`, `azureProject`, `repositoryId`, and `prUrlBase`. Do NOT hardcode these values.

## PR URL Format

```
<config.project.prUrlBase>/<pullRequestId>
```

## Git Remote

The remote `origin` points to Azure DevOps. Standard `git push` / `git fetch` / `git pull` work normally.
